                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm abhored by the idea of neo agreeing with me as is obvious by his earlier posts he has very little knowledge of how to play an enc efficiently.
<br />

<br />
What i said was in no way a support of the charm nerf which i vehemently oppose, and to the best of my knowledge this isnt a viable technique in oow.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I still think pullin as an enc is a viable teqhnique in oow, but its very different, much less forgiving rules.  
<br />
On an hourly basis, because i'm not working with tools more specifically designed for pulling, i will take more hits than an equivalently skilled bard or monk.  I also mitigate worse, meaning the hits i do take incur more dmg to the group's resources.
<br />
Addly as we lack FD/Fade, the overpull in oow is you try to stay out of camp and root one of the incoming mobs as basically your best scenario, and that's a crapshoot @ best.  In an equivalent sutiation a monk or bard would have a very easy time.  The add'ly death related downtime(i prolly die bout once every 2-3 hours pulling mpg, whereas i just dont die there as bard.) is once again making you a less efficient puller.
<br />

<br />
Encs can still make ground vs pulling classes, but it's not on the level of class skills.(well, i sorta lied, root's the most underappreciated spell i know, it's a tossup between root and tash for my fav spell, and the other comes in 2nd, in large because of how well they work hand-in-hand... but i could write a whole thesis on the usage of root, so i'll just skip that topic for the moment)
<br />

<br />
I personally try to make up the inefficiencys of the class by timing everthings(repops, aa/screyers refresh, debuffs, and buffs) i've got my /loc parsed onto a map, and verbal warnings on root break as well as a couple other lines that are useful to be instantly aware of.  
<br />
I've got better gear than the avg player on my server(8.5k hp buffed) and have clickies suited for pulling(clicky mem-blur, dispell, and of course, bcb).
<br />
Now, this can make -me- a better choice for a group than random_bard_01, but a bard or monk who cares about their game as much as i do will blow me out of the water(post oow, pre-oow, i can give em a run for their money)
<br />

<br />
so... what does this all mean in the end?
<br />
Can you pull in oow: prolly
<br />
is it a wise choice:prolly not unless you have some very extenuating circumstances.(i should honestly switch mains to the 70 bard i inherited as it's simply a better toon for the job, but i just cant bring myself to give up khyla, emotional attchement after spending so many hour n such)</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
