                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">About the original poster, nothing summarizes better than what Mezrin said (see quote below)
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Thus individuals coming to the Runes and making volatile posts with negativity, which insult the views of those who are upset about these issues, have been greeted with less than normal tolerance. Rav is entitled to his views, but he needs to make them in a less confrontation manner because the enchanter community as a whole is not in the mood to be called "whiners" in light of recent events. This is all we have asked. Not that he change his views, but that he be less confrontational about it. It is not alot to ask, and is not unreasonable.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
That pretty much says it all, no ifs, buts, or ands about it. While at it, I would like to emphasized the words "volatil posts", "confrontation manner" and "in light of recent events" because that seems to be the norm for post where the original poster only intent is looking forward to spark arguments and angry responses.
<br />

<br />
As an example, if you make a joke about somebody´s wife sex-life to the husband, you are gonna get punched in the eye. More so, if you were to make the joke to the husband right after you know he found out the wife was cheating on him, then it doesn´t take a brain surgeon to realize that yes, it is going to get ugly.
<br />

<br />
That´s what the original poster did, his post is nothing but a joke, aimed at sparking anger. Any later attemps at trying to be civil are still a joke, on top of insulting everyone else´s intelligence.
<br />

<br />
That said, and since once again people keep talking about the same dead horse over and over, my views about chanter boredom and chanter cancellation accounts are already spoken for by others in this thread. It basically comes down to:
<br />

<br />
1- CC is no longer REQUIRED. While having pullers pull adds so that they can be lined up increases group efficiency a tiny little bit, the only real reason for doing so is to indulge the chanter boredom. Still, planned adds aren´t the same in terms of thrills. 
<br />

<br />
Heck, with the mobs stopping to attack when under 20% and snared, even a tank can manage to step out and pull something else. From PoP on pretty much everyone can pull singles. Ask monks.
<br />

<br />
2- OOW Charm is USELESS as is. The only time I have OOW Charm memmed is when an SK is tank to cover for assist fook ups. A 200 hitter mob that breaks and hits the group for 800-1000 in MPG for instance is slowing your group down. Again, if a group indulges you to have a charmed pet, thank them, for you are not making them any favors, quite the contrary. Most camps in MPG don´t have much space to put between you and your pet.
<br />

<br />

<br />
If pet is hasted, you better pray you land a Tash between 2 secs when breaking, else you might end up looking for rezzes for your cleric all over the zone, as well as other party members. And even if the ex pet charges at you (while snared), the best case scenario is that you spend 1 or 2 secs for Tash, another 2 or so for snare to land and get confirmation message, and then 4 more seconds for your charm to land, plus another 2 for pet to be back at mauling the other mob for said 200 HPs. Totaling 10 secs. 
<br />

<br />
Add to that that you need to have a snarer in camp at all times (ranja/druid) and a slower (shaman/Beast Lord), so that recharming is done as fast as possible while mob at camp gets slowed. The longer the ex-pet remains uncharmed, the higher the chances of a member going splat. Specially if you hasted the pet. You can sub the shammy requirement with mezzing the ex-pet and slowing the freshly pull mob, should it happen at the same time, but that just adds more pet downtime.
<br />

<br />
3- No CC + no CHARM = BOREDOM. Most chanters didn´t make their character to slow mobs and nuke like a level 49 wiz. This is the main chanter complain, CHARM just made PoP a little bearable, nothing more (when grouping at least)
<br />

<br />
I sure didn´t level my chanter to 70, got 600+ AAs, 7.5K mana and 9K HPs with raid buffs to slow and nuke. I would have made a shaman if so, which has a better pet, solos well, has better and fastest casting slow, buffes group STATS like no other class, which amounts to 1K extra HPs, has unlimited mana, can sub for main healer (while not your average Joe, when I group with 2 guildie friends in Riftseekers, shaman and zerker, one is main healer and the other main tank), and shaman has way better DPS with dots than us.
<br />

<br />
In fact, if they would just given us DC pets in all OOW zones, and maybe even raise DC cap to 50, a good number of us would just be content, even if no OOW charm spell was given to us at all (or nerfed as it is).
<br />

<br />
Our main grief with charm is that it gave us something to do, not the DPS of said charm, most would have been ok with a 50% reduction. A DC pet would fill the role of giving us something to do during the 2+ hours that go by before you have to mez again.
<br />

<br />
All chanter rants can be summed up as a cry to SoE saying "Give us something to do!". It can be by actually giving us something "new" *cough*, like the DC pet idea (balancing DC? LOL), or by redesigning content so mez is again needed. See mez as any form of mez, pet ghetto mez, root mez, offtanking by monks/BL/ranjas (yes it means more adds and mobs hitting for less), snare kite, more undeads so necros can use mez, etc.
<br />

<br />
It is easy to cheer on charm nerf or remain indifferent, when it really doesn´t affect you at all. You get to know this when you lose something you cared.
<br />

<br />
There were all kinds of woohoos when bards got the AE nerf on this board. I play a level 70 Bard with 400AAs and about to become awesome when I finish getting her the rest of my Qvic armor. But bard an all, I never much cared about AE, found it extremely boring and liked much more to charm swarm instead. Because of this, I didn´t post anything one way or another. It just didn´t affect me.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
